    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In colonial Latin America, oidores were ministers of justice of the Real Audiencia of the Spanish court, who listened and passed judgment on civil cases.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
